    <h1>Cross-selling</h1><div id="preamble">
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In cross-selling, you subtly encourage customers to spend more money. This is done by offering additional products that relate to the purchased product. Just a few examples:</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p>The cashier at a fast food restaurant asks if you want fries with your cheeseburger.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>The salesman in an electronics store suggests a memory card that would work with the digital camera.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In a shoe store, the sales clerk asks if you want to buy a shoe polish to properly care for your new shoes.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In e-commerce, you can’t directly ask your customers if they want to buy additional products. However, you can display a list of related items on the product pages in your online store.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In just three easy steps, you can generate additional sales through cross-selling.
First, make sure that your items meet the <a href="/en/item/online-store/cross-selling#100">requirements for cross-selling</a>.
Then create <a href="/en/item/online-store/cross-selling#200">cross-selling links</a> in plentymarkets.
Finally, publish the <a href="/en/item/online-store/cross-selling#700">list of related items in your online store</a>.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Other cross-selling service providers</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The external service provider <a href="/en/online-store/online-store/extras/yoochoose">YOOCHOOSE</a> offers an alternative to plentymarkets cross-selling.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="100">1. Requirements</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The following requirements have to be met in order for direct cross-selling items to be displayed in your online store:</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p><a href="/en/item/online-store/checklist-categories-visibility">The cross-selling item’s category must be activated</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><a href="/en/item/online-store/checklist-items-visibility">The item must be visible in the online store</a>.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Do you have a Callisto store?</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If you use an older Callisto store, then you’ll also need to configure a few additional settings.
Go to <strong>Setup » Client » Select client » Online store » Settings</strong> and use the <strong>Cross-selling</strong> setting to specify <a href="/en/online-store/online-store/item-sorting#_setting_up_cross_selling_templates">which type of cross-selling</a> you want to use.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Then use the <strong>Dynamic cross-selling</strong> setting to specify whether you want to use so-called <a href="/en/online-store/online-store/item-sorting#_setting_up_dynamic_cross_selling">dynamic cross-selling</a>. In this case, items will automatically be linked to each other if customers have purchased them at the same time.
Please note that dynamic cross-selling is only possible with older Callisto stores.
It is not currently possible to set up dynamic cross-selling for newer Ceres stores.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="200">2. Cross-selling links</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Are you ready to start linking your items together?
There are a few different ways to create and edit cross-selling links.
For example, you can <a href="/en/item/online-store/cross-selling#250">manually create and edit links</a> directly within an item data record.
Or you can enter information about the cross-selling links into a CSV file and then <a href="/en/item/online-store/cross-selling#650">import this file into plentymarkets</a>.</p>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="250">2.1. Manually creating and editing links</h3>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="300">2.1.1. Creating new links</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Which items should be linked together? You can link an item to any number of other products from your portfolio. For example, imagine you want to link a guitar to a pack of replacement strings, a song book and a guitar strap.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Linking a main item to accessories:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Item » Edit item</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><a href="/en/item/introduction/search#100">Search for</a> and open the main item, e.g. the guitar.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the tab <strong>Cross-selling » Add item(s)</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Search for items again in this tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select all the accessories (<span class="icon blue"><i class="fa fa-check-square  "></i></span>) that should be linked to the main item, e.g. select the replacement strings, the song book and the guitar strap.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the appropriate relationship (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-cubes  "></i></span>). Note <a href="#table-cross-selling-relationship">Table 1</a>.<br>
→ The links will be created and they <a href="/en/item/online-store/cross-selling#600">can be changed any time</a>.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
